The paper deals with a robotics problem of searching for a target on a line, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves designing search algorithms, which can be seen as an artificial intelligence problem (cs.AI). The paper also considers different robot mobility models, which involve analyzing and manipulating data structures (cs.DS). The objective of achieving good competitive ratios involves optimization, which falls under the scope of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves deriving optimal algorithms, which can be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG).
